2. 1: HTML :
• Create an HTML file named "index.html" with a simple form that allows users to input text into three
separate fields.

code: 


<html>

<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
    <title>Simple Form</title>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="form-container">
    <h2>Simple Form:-</h2>
      <form action="#" method="POST">
        <label for="fname">First name:</label>
        <input type="text" id="first-name" name="first name" required ><br><br>
        
        <label for="lname">Last name:</label>
        <input type="text" id="last name" name="last name" required ><br><br>
      
        <label for="email">Email:</label>
        <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required ><br><br><br>
      
        <button type="button" onclick="alert('Form Submitted')">Submit</button>
      </form>
   </div> 
</body>

</html>

2:CSS

• Style the form using a CSS file named "styles.css" to make it visually appealing.







